						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ⎯⎯ Year: ⎯⎯</hi></p>						

						<p>This record states that Basavaṇasōmayāji of Chauṭakūr and Timmappa of Gōraṇṭi, the <hi rend="italic">bāgila-sēnabōva</hi> of Virapaṇṇayya got written all the stone characters in the temple of the goddess Mahālakshmi of Lakhkhaṇāpura. For this they obtained the consent of Penugoṇḍe Virapaṇṇayya.</p>						

